M remains out of active hours.\n- 02h is stronger than a dead hour stereotype would suggest:\n  - **38** tracked windows\n  - **18** with `|bias| >= 45`\n  - **11** with `|bias| >= 55`\n  - max bias **68.7**\n- Most of 02h stayed in a single familiar regime:\n  - `(0.505, 0.495)` \u2192 **33** windows\n  - `(0.475, 0.525)` \u2192 **5** windows\n- Importantly, price is **not** the main blocker here:\n  - rich-price incidents in logged OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS windows: **0**\n  - explicit `Price too high` events in 02h: only **1**\n- So 02h is not being excluded because the market is constantly too rich or structurally untradeable.\n- The real blocker is still validation:\n  - no direct validated YES-trade outcomes for these overnight hours\n  - historically, the overnight bucket underperformed badly\n  - current live-quality overnight tape is interesting, but unproven\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis distinction matters. If 02h were failing because of terrible pricing, we could safely dismiss it as untradeable. But that is not what tonight shows. 02h is showing decent market access",
